video_title: Team Trip to 'Oli w Music by Kalei & Suar
description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
'Oli Ukulele is designed by me and Ryan and built in Bandung on the Island of Java by a group that has been making guitars for over 65 years and ukuleles for 20 now. Last week I brought lead luthier Ryan Condon, head of our setup team Joel Blechinger, and of course Kalei Gamiao to work with the team there for the week. 
All songs are original jams by Kalei and the song with Suar is one of his originals, "Dewasa". Aside from being our head luthier in Bandung, Suar Nasution is also a talented songwriter and performer! The songs from Kalei were just made up in the hotel room or outside of the factory, just playing what he feels and being awesome like always.
Joel worked with the team on setups and proper install for two new pickups we will start using, the GOAA and the new Mi-Si motif. Ryan braced out two new guitars, one classical and the other a small body steel so stay tuned for those. 
This video follows a somewhat chronological order of the build from the kiln drying process, marking out and cutting up wood sets, putting it together and the finish and setup. Basically just a music video with peeks into the process and shots from the everyday work going on at the factory. I just threw this together in a day to get back to work but hope you enjoy and let us know with any questions. See you soon with more ukes and music. Aloha!
Song 1 - X2-TTSRBW Torrefied Spruce Black and White Rosewood X braced Tenor 
Song 2 - L2-CMR Tiger Myrtle Concert
Song 3 - X2-TCRBW Cedar Black and White Rosewood X braced Tenor 
Song 4 - X2-BCPW Port Orford Cedar Walnut Baritone
Song 5 w Suar on L3-BTSE-HC Torrefied Spruce Ebony Honeycomb Baritone & Kalei on 
Song 6 - X2-TCRBW Cedar Black and White Rosewood X braced Tenor

video_title: 25.7 Kalei's New Song - Corey's New Guitar - Ko'olau New Bracing
description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
This is the first of a limited Kanazawa series from Ko'olau. It has a totally different bracing from what we've previously seen and sounds incredible. 
It has elements of lattice bracing and even elements of Pepe's skin bracing but it's entirely its own thing. Really cool and we love it. Should be up on the site in the next day or so.
I feel like Kalei and Corey are sitting on a few albums worth of ideas and none of us have much time but it's nice to release something here again for you guys. This is a quick take on a still untitled song from Kalei. 
And Corey's guitar, how cool is that. I think I was spraying that one 23 years ago. Did so many Martin refinishes I don't even remember but wow such a great little steel string. Anyway, share your thoughts and we'll be back with more vibrations and creations. Aloha!

video_title: 'Oli Ukulele Factory Visit w Kalei Gamiao
description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
This last week Kalei and I went to another volcanic island across the pacific, Java, and to the wonderful city of Bandung. We checked in on the development of our new line, ‚ÄòOli, and documented some of that here for you. 

Husni Nasution started Genta Guitars in 1959 with a goal to make high quality musical instruments. A few decades ago my father started working with him and his sons, Awan and Suar, teaching them about ‚Äòukulele and creating the Pono line of ukulele and guitar. Hunsi passed away some years back and now that my father has retired, this is a 2nd generation collaboration between our two families on a new line, ‚ÄòOli. 

The culture and warmth of the people in this factory and around the city of Bandung is always astounding to me. There‚Äôs truly an Aloha spirit and the effort put in by all of us collectively will ensure that ‚ÄòOli delivers its meaning, joy and happiness. 

All NEW original song ideas from Kalei! (Pretty cool stuff, right?!) All three instruments played are tenors. The first is from the Hawaiian Koa line, the second is a cedar top Macassar ebony, and the third is an all quilted maple. (Recording w a travel recorder, we'll come with our regular sound samples soon for proper comparing)

Talks are with Suar Nasition (His brother Awan runs the company as well and I‚Äôll have to interview him next time) And also with Derry Surya Ganda Permana, manager of quality control.

Hope you enjoy! Let us know your thoughts and mahalo for watching and sharing!

The Lili‚Äòu Project presents Makalapua, the latest in an ongoing series of performances that feature Queen Lili‚Äòuokalani‚Äôs mele in novel ways. The project is dedicated to investigating Lili ªuokalani‚Äôs music and memoirs, guided by her own free-spirited innovation and interest in contemporary trends. This multifaceted production explores the emotional and spiritual influence her compositions have had, and continue to have.

description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
We've been too busy to put out much content lately so I had my friend Allan come in Friday afternoon and shoot some of what goes on in a day over here. Joel was out but otherwise, the crew was in, small but strong. A huge part of our work is improving the instruments we send. Other than that we're just trying to help you get what you want and need. Mahalo for all of your support throughout the years!  
Aloha!

Lots of Kamaka will be listed at the website from now through next week. Really excited about this batch. Gorgeous sounds and beautiful koa from the Hawaiian ohana that has been providing the world with great ukes for 105 years. Hope you enjoy the episode. Let us know how we can help with anything ukulele and see you next time. Aloha!

video_title: 21.13 KoAloha Ukulele w Alan & Paul Okami
description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
Kalei wasn't able to make it Thursday night but came down the following night to record so I mixed these recordings in. Kalei has been entirely tied up with restoring his property after the flood in Haleiwa. If you are able, there is a fundraiser for them and their neighbors here- https://www.gofundme.com/f/wra6km-aloha-for-gamiao-ohana
The instruments demoed through most of this podcast are from the KoAloha  Napaka series made with half koa and half mango. This series is rare to show up and we just got new models in soprano concert and tenor and they sound incredible! Look out for those to hit the site in the next day or two. 
The duets tonight were just 'jams" or mash-ups of various songs over a few chords.

video_title: 20.24 Robi Kahakalau & Kala'e Camarillo
description:
Robi and Kala'e are two of Hawaii's most wonderful and extremely talented musicians, so this was a great time. We dig into Sistah Robi's adventurous life & illustrious musical career with Hawaiian Style Band and other legendary musicians. Joining us again, the multi-instrument, singer-songwriter, & music teacher, Kala'e Camarillo, showcasing a unique and beautiful Hawaiian duo. 
Mike Love jumps into the conversation in the 2nd half too :)
I had some technical issues on this one but Robi and Kala'e are so good it hardly matters. Recording these sessions is a work in progress. Mahalo for watching, sharing, & supporting. These are made possible by https://www.theukulelesite.com 
Aloha!

video_title: 20.19 Rama & son Kala'e Camarillo (Happy Fathers Day!)
description:
We start this one off w a duet "How Deep is Your Love" from Kala'e Camarillo & Mika Kane. 
The Camarillo ohana has been crucial for over 50 years in teaching the keiki of Hawai'i ukulele. You can learn more about their family from this short film https://youtu.be/9GgJAqP5vJ8
You can see the 2nd Sundays performance from the KapƒÅlama Elementary Ukulele Band Kala'e teaches here https://youtu.be/owV-yALVNXI
It was great having these two talents, Rama & his son Kala'e,  share music with you guys on fathers day. Aloha, and mahalo for your support. https://www.theukulelesite.com

video_title: Ep. 19.34 Billy on Ukulele Setup & Corey Kalei Duo
description:
https://www.theukulelesite.com
So this week we decided to focus on the setup team and interview one of our luthiers, Billy Dominick. Also, Corey and Kalei play a few songs as they create the set for their Asian tour. They do a killer Beatles Medley that starts at 12:36. 

Because I had brought up Mauna Kea I thought I would give some details for those not aware, and maybe interested. Mauna Kea is the tallest mountain in Hawaii and when measured at its ocean base, the tallest in the world. It has always been sacred to the Native Hawaiians and many cultural and religious practices are still performed there. What they are now protesting is plans to put in a Thirty Meter Telescope (TMT) The glass is 30 meters in diameter making it 3 times as wide, 9 times larger than the largest existing visible-light telescope to date and 18 stories high. Talking about the better part of a football field for just the size of the telescope and a few acres of property to house it right at the top of sacred ground. Protestors are not against science. They just don‚Äôt want that humongous structure and all the activity it brings on a mountain that holds their cultural history. 

I wanted to add a note here that Kalei sent me. He is part Hawaiian. His great grandfather was one of the designers of the Hawaiian flag actually, an immigrant from England that married a Hawaii princess. Anyway, Kalei said, ‚ÄúThirst for knowledge is one thing but not at the cost of people's beliefs, culture, tradition. I feel a ton for the police force. They are probably hurting more than most people think. Also every single person that calls Hawaii their home. This issue seems to go far beyond being a native Hawaiian from the land.‚Äù

I agree that this issue should matter to all people here. Because the need is for respect to indigenous culture. As far as I can tell this disregard has gone on too long. Intergenerational trauma has boiled to the surface. The people are taking back their power. I feel like I should have either not brought it up or given it more time because it is important, so I wanted to add here. Humility and respect from me. Just wanted to share some thoughts. Aloha 

#TheUkuleleReview

video_title: Luthiers for a Cause - 6 Custom Ukulele Makers - Sound Samples and Discussion
description:
This is a charity project from some of the finest ukulele makers. They each built a custom tenor out of the same amazing woods and we will be auctioning them off at https://theukulelesite.com for a non-profit, Ukulele Kids Club, who provides ukuleles and music therapy to kids dealing with major medical problems. This fund raising is all arranged and done through the organization, Luthiers for a Cause. 

Featured ukuleles and interview with Kevin Beddoe of Kinnard Ukes, legendary guitar maker Steve Grimes, Jay Lichty, Beau Hannam, Jake Maclay, and Joji Yoshida. From the east coast to Japan, these are some of the best uke builders out there. Apply competent giving us dry sound samples to enjoy, we start with Kimo Hussey, then Corey Fujimoto, and end with Kalei Gamio. 

Big mahalos to all involved and all who support this upcoming effort. Auction should start soon. Aloha!

description:

So that's what we did and I get to know him here and get to experience these very special custom tenor ukes along with you. Enjoy!!
Aloha from all of us here at http://theukulelesite.com
Subscribe and stay touch. A hui ho!

Oh I should mention because we were doing true sound samples there is no compression so try listen on good headphones or speakers to best hear the tones. Hopefully we see a lot more of Pat's instruments.

description:
http://theukulelesite.com
So for you guys just used to our Youtube videos our podcasts aren't really entertaining in the way those are. It's long and just a bunch of talking heads but if you want to learn how to do some setup work yourself this might help. We have a thorough setup video on our process that we do to all ukes we ship out here - https://youtu.be/Elfo9xHPhZE.
Our podcast "The Ukulele Review" is fairly new but we've been trying to do one each week and have other episodes covering various uke topics and featuring different builders and players. You can find that here on itunes - https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/the-ukulele-review-podcast/id1118340956?mt=2 Subscribe, rate, and comment there. We also have another setup podcast there covering various issues and talking with the full setup team. Mahalo for tuning in. See you next time.

description:

video_title: #27 Tobias Elof - aNueNue, 3 Hive Ukes, Reggae Beat Tutorial, Humidifier Test+
description:
https://theukulelesite.com
Great having Tobias back to play music and talk. Corey Fujimoto of course backing him up on guitars some. Listen to Tobias last album on spotify here https://spoti.fi/2Hsdj72
Hive ukes going up on the site soon. (So nice!)
As far as the humidifier test, I still have to record the details and make a summary on http://theukulelereview.com. It has a few anomalies as well  I didn't get into here so I'll try to break it down sometime in the next few days. In any case, the Oasis seemed most effective but I really liked the Humistat too. I'm experimenting for my own knowledge. I feel a responsibility to learn and share when it comes to protecting your investments. And I'm  gonna keep testing different systems and situations.
Mahalo for checking out our channel. Support Tobias Elof by getting and sharing his music. Aloha!
